<br>
On one of the late raid corpse runs I had my very first fall into the lava pit <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Lol, After countless warnings to others, I finally manged to do it myself.  Figures it would be during a Raid situation.<br>
<br>
Then I pulled the Ultimate Stupid.  Instead of staying where i was and accepting my fate, I tried to find a way out.  So i started swimming around looking for an exit.  Well the lava pit has lava falls, which are one way and you cannot get back up them. DOH!!  So i think &quot;now im even more screwed because i wont be able to summon my body from this far away.  So what do i do?  I KEEP SWIMMING FURTHER AWAY!!  Am i just asking for a nasty body recovery or what??<br>
<br>
My LoH was up and i was at almost full health when i fell in,  So mind you I had a LOT of time to swim around.  For some reason Falling into a pit of Scalding hot Molten rock and Magma doesnt kill you as quick as you think it would.  So i use up my LoH and continue to swim.  What is the next thing to happen you ask?  Well i zoned into SOLB!!!!  Gah!!  Didnt know there was a zonline in lava <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Now not only am I swimming around in Lava, But im in the Worst Corpse Recovery  zone in the Old World.  And guess what??  my last hitpoints have Just faded and my body has given up the Ghost.  Bleaaargh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Luckily Athame was able to come to my rescue for a summon.  Yaaaay Athame!!  My sincerest thanks for your help that day.   <br>
 Which reminds me,  things were kind of hectic during that period and I cant quite remember if I supplied you with a coffin, and/or reimbursed you for the use of one.  I thought i did but this Old brain of mine keeps getting Fuzzy on me.  Let me Know if I did or not.<br>
<br>
Also many thanks to Phaith who answered my pleas for rezzes.  And who even managed to cast one for me, even while company was knocking on the door in RL.  Many Many thanks all around.  Especially to those who showed up and participated in the event.  I had a blast.  Truly i did.  The body run was the least of my concerns, and i hope you all had as good a time as I.<br>
<br>
Yours Truly,<br>
Montag <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E8fA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=paithansylva>PaithanSylva</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#000080>(1/28/03 3:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My thanks to Montag and Arrow!</span><hr size=1> ohhh,.. this is a good post,.. not ofcourse becouse Montag died,.. sorry to hear that. But i somehow always thought that lava=instant death. As this is not the case,.. I (as a druid) can simply gate out in case I ever fall in. Thanks for this info!<br>
